From: Sur <sur@localhost>
Date: Wed Jun 24 11:20:00 2026
Subject: [PATCH] remove select REGULATOR_VIRTUAL_CONSUMER from AXP2101 regulator

The AXP2101 PMIC regulator driver selects REGULATOR_VIRTUAL_CONSUMER
which is a debugging/testing driver that causes "DMA mask not set"
warnings and has no functional benefit. Remove the select to allow
disabling it in the config.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [BSP-specific]
Signed-off-by: Sur <sur@localhost>

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/power/Kconfig b/bsp/drivers/power/Kconfig
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/bsp/drivers/power/Kconfig
+++ b/bsp/drivers/power/Kconfig
@@ -96,7 +96,6 @@ config AW_REGULATOR_AXP2101
 	tristate "X-POWERS AXP2101 PMIC Regulators"
 	depends on AW_MFD_AXP2101
 	select REGULATOR
-	select REGULATOR_VIRTUAL_CONSUMER
 	help
 	  This driver provides support for the voltage regulators on the
 	  AXP2101 PMIC.
